            <p class="text-justify">Titan Airlines is a United Kingdom-based charter airline that was founded in 1988. Its main hub is at the London Stansted Airport. Some of their clients are Air Malta, Brussels Airlines, Condor, SAS, Wizz Air, etc. Titan Airways does not have scheduled flights, but they carry out charter flight services for their clients. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">You should note that you should preorder your ticket if you are planning a trip. If you preorder the ticket, you will get a great deal at a very low price. If you need to buy an emergency ticket for, let's say, the next day, you will see the ticket price is too high. This is the reason one should preorder a <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/">flight ticket</a>. </p>
            <h2>Refund Policy </h2>
            <p class="text-justify">Titan Airways does not have a <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/refund-policy.aspx">refund policy</a> of its own, but they work according to the laws. According to this law, EC261, if some circumstances are met, you are eligible for compensation (refund). In the case of Titan Airways, if you had a flight from Eu, you canceled the flight at least 14 hours before the takeoff, and if the flight is late at least for a minimum of 3 hours, then you are entitled to get the <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/titan-airways-refund-policy.aspx">Titan Airways Flight Compensation</a>. </p>
            <h3>Frequently asked question</h3>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Who can receive a refund with Titan Airways? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">According to the Law of EC261, if you are to board a flight from the EU and have canceled the ticket at least before 14 hours from its takeoff or if the flight is late for a minimum of 3 hours, then you are entitled to a getting the “Titan Airways Flight Compensation” which acts like the refund. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How can I cancel a flight ticket with Titan Airways? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can visit the travel agency company if you booked the ticket offline and ask them to cancel it. If you ordered it via online then visit the website through which you ordered it and then cancel it. It is as easy as it gets. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Where can I make the request for a refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">Once you cancelled your ticket 14 hours before it’s take off then you will get the compensation/refund on the payment mode you used to make the payment while booking the ticket. For example, if you paid with a credit card, you will get a refund back into your credit card. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Will I get any compensation from Titan airways if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You will only get a refund if your flight gets delayed for a minimum of 3 hours. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Is my flight refundable? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">Yes, your flight is refundable if they meets certain conditions like if you are to board a flight from the EU and have canceled the ticket at least before 14 hours from its takeoff or if the flight is late for a minimum of 3 hours, then you are entitled to a getting the "Titan Airways Flight Compensation" which acts like the refund. </p>

